Abstract:
  In this paper, the authors analyze the speed of convergence to a balanced
 path in a class of endogenous growth models with physical and human
 capital. They show that such rate depends locally on the technological
 parameters of the model but does not depend on preferences parameters.
 This result stands in sharp contrast with that of the one-sector
 neoclassical growth model, where both preferences and technologies
 determine the speed of convergence to a steady-state growth path.   Copyright 1997 by American Economic Association.
