Author-Name:    Anderson, Lisa R
Author-Name:  Holt, Charles A
Title:   Information Cascades in the Laboratory. 
Journal: American Economic Review
Pages: 847-62
Issue: 5
Volume: 87
Year: 1997
Month:  December 
Abstract:
  When a series of individuals with private information announce public
 predictions, initial conformity can create an 'information cascade' in
 which later predictions match the early announcements. This paper reports
 an experiment in which private signals are draws from an unobserved urn.
 Subjects make predictions in sequence and are paid if they correctly guess
 which of two urns was used for the draws. If initial decisions coincide,
 then it is rational for subsequent decisionmakers to follow the
 established pattern, regardless of their private information. Rational
 cascades formed in most periods in which such an imbalance occurred.   Copyright 1997 by American Economic Association.
